18:14.959 --> 18:16.060
HENRY: Sorry.

18:14.959 --> 18:16.060
GRADY: I got it.

18:16.094 --> 18:17.762
HENRY: Ow.

18:17.796 --> 18:20.699
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

18:23.969 --> 18:26.471
HENRY:<i> Please.
I'm being serious.</i>

18:23.969 --> 18:26.471
CLAY:<i> Don't worry.</i>

18:26.504 --> 18:27.706
HENRY:<i> Ow.</i>

18:31.008 --> 18:33.245
HENRY:<i> I don't want...please.</i>

18:33.278 --> 18:34.980
<i> Please.</i>

18:33.278 --> 18:34.980
[MUFFLED] What's wrong?

18:35.013 --> 18:36.814
CLAY:<i> You'll get wet soon.</i>

18:36.848 --> 18:38.250
HENRY:<i> Get the...get the...</i>

18:38.283 --> 18:40.785
CLAY:<i> Jesus, Henry.</i>

18:38.283 --> 18:40.785
GRADY: Henry.

18:40.819 --> 18:42.187
HENRY:<i> Get the fuck off of me!</i>

18:42.220 --> 18:44.722
[OBJECTS RATTLING]

18:44.756 --> 18:46.658
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

18:46.691 --> 18:50.261
[OBJECTS CRASHING]

18:50.294 --> 18:51.897
[GRUNTING]

18:50.294 --> 18:51.897
[WHOOSHING]

18:54.466 --> 18:55.934
Henry?

18:55.967 --> 18:57.736
[WHOOSHING]

18:59.204 --> 19:02.307
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

19:20.625 --> 19:24.095
CLEO: Henry, I thought
you were at work.

19:24.128 --> 19:25.898
I gotta go.
I'm gonna be late.

19:35.374 --> 19:38.709
<i> Yeah, so then I installed
these really cool RGB lights,</i>

19:38.743 --> 19:40.979
<i> and also this arm
has a rotating wrist,</i>

19:41.013 --> 19:42.748
<i> which is awesome.</i>

19:42.781 --> 19:44.282
Cool.

19:44.316 --> 19:47.285
<i> Hey, is that
the</i> Enterprise NCC-1701-E?

19:47.319 --> 19:50.989
Okay, some people think
it's the<i> Enterprise D.</i>

19:51.022 --> 19:52.557
<i> With that engine chamber?</i>

19:52.591 --> 19:53.992
[CHUCKLES]

19:54.025 --> 19:56.695
[ALARM BEEPING]

19:54.025 --> 19:56.695
Oh.

19:56.728 --> 20:00.032
I have to go to bed,
but my mom wants to know

20:00.065 --> 20:03.901
if you have any dietary
restrictions or food allergies.

20:03.935 --> 20:06.404
I already told her, no walnuts.

20:06.438 --> 20:07.973
<i> We're good, then.</i>

20:08.006 --> 20:09.474
<i> Are you sure
you're cool with me</i>

20:09.507 --> 20:11.243
<i> crashing your
family game night?</i>

20:11.276 --> 20:13.778
Yes, my parents like
when I have company,

20:13.812 --> 20:17.482
but you can't be game master
on your first visit.

20:17.515 --> 20:19.584
And if we play
<i> Settlers of Catan,</i>

20:19.617 --> 20:22.387
you can't build a road
through an enemy's settlement.

20:22.420 --> 20:24.522
It's a common mistake.

20:24.556 --> 20:26.191
<i> Why would I waste my time
building roads</i>

20:26.224 --> 20:27.659
<i> when I know the Knight Cards</i>

20:27.692 --> 20:29.327
<i> get me just
as many victory points</i>

20:29.360 --> 20:30.962
<i> and I control the Robber?</i>

20:30.995 --> 20:32.730
Okay.

20:32.764 --> 20:34.565
[CHUCKLES]

20:34.599 --> 20:36.234
[CHUCKLES]
I'll see you Saturday.

20:36.267 --> 20:37.369
I love you.

20:37.402 --> 20:39.004
<i> I love you, too.</i>

20:40.071 --> 20:41.373
[COMPUTER CHIMES]

20:49.381 --> 20:51.916
<i>For fuck's sake, kid,
stop clicking on random links.</i>

20:51.950 --> 20:54.419
<i> No, I'm not hacking
your computer again.</i>

20:54.452 --> 20:56.521
Go away!
I'm not a part of this anymore!

20:56.554 --> 20:58.323
<i> If you're talking,
I can't hear you,</i>

20:58.356 --> 21:00.225
<i> because if you are
watching this, I'm dead,</i>

21:00.258 --> 21:01.659
<i>probably for a couple days now,</i>

21:01.693 --> 21:04.096
<i> if this fail-safe shit
actually worked.</i>

21:04.129 --> 21:06.732
<i> All my other contacts
are dead, too,</i>

21:06.765 --> 21:10.302
<i>so you're the closest thing
I have to a protege by default,</i>

21:10.335 --> 21:12.270
<i> and I'm leaving you
my life's work.</i>

21:12.303 --> 21:15.140
<i> Well, the work
of my middle age.</i>

21:15.173 --> 21:16.875
<i> Everything I have
on the teleporters</i>

21:16.908 --> 21:18.943
<i> and their operations.</i>

21:18.977 --> 21:21.747
<i> Obviously they got to me
before I could stop them.</i>

21:22.914 --> 21:24.916
<i> Listen.</i>
[SIGHS]

21:24.949 --> 21:27.485
<i> I didn't plan on getting
involved in this shit.</i>

21:27.518 --> 21:29.788
<i> I was just in the wrong place
at the wrong time,</i>

21:29.821 --> 21:33.324
<i> and I decided to do
the right thing.</i>

21:33.357 --> 21:38.163
<i> Just don't let this
fuck you over like me.</i>

21:38.196 --> 21:42.100
<i> No family, no friends.</i>

21:42.134 --> 21:44.169
<i>Christ, it's not lost on me
that I'm sending my last words</i>

21:44.202 --> 21:46.704
<i> to some kid
I met fucking once.</i>

21:46.738 --> 21:49.474
<i> Okay, I'm sending you
encrypted coordinates</i>

21:49.507 --> 21:50.875
<i> and a lock code.</i>

21:50.908 --> 21:53.044
<i> I want you to memorize it
and then delete them,</i>

21:53.077 --> 21:54.446
<i> and then delete this.</i>

21:56.514 --> 21:58.316
<i> And good luck, kid.</i>

21:58.350 --> 22:00.485
Valar morghulis.

22:04.856 --> 22:06.925
Valar dohaeris.

22:13.365 --> 22:16.068
[GENTLE MUSIC]

22:45.063 --> 22:47.932
[WHOOSHING]

22:47.966 --> 22:50.168
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

22:50.201 --> 22:51.703
[GROANS]

23:17.428 --> 23:19.397
[KNOCK AT DOOR]

23:19.431 --> 23:22.567
[TENSE MUSIC]

23:28.940 --> 23:30.041
What happened?

23:30.074 --> 23:33.044
Had a panic attack and ended up
in my fucking room.

23:33.077 --> 23:34.413
Somebody hurt you?

23:35.947 --> 23:37.114
No.

23:37.148 --> 23:39.050
No one did anything.

23:40.885 --> 23:42.854
I just...

23:42.887 --> 23:44.823
I just felt like I was back
in that fucking truck

23:44.856 --> 23:46.992
like the first time,
and I'm just mad,

23:47.025 --> 23:50.328
because I thought I was
past this shit.

23:50.361 --> 23:53.031
It gets worse before it gets
better, if that's any comfort.

23:53.064 --> 23:54.732
It's not.

23:54.766 --> 23:57.402
What if your sister uses
that fake room
against me and...

23:57.435 --> 23:59.237
I took care of it,
I told you.

23:59.270 --> 24:00.337
Yeah, but what
does that mean?

24:00.371 --> 24:01.673
It's fine.

24:01.706 --> 24:03.575
We wouldn't be here
if it wasn't, trust me.

24:08.446 --> 24:10.448
I'm just...

24:10.482 --> 24:13.384
[GENTLE MUSIC]

24:13.417 --> 24:15.186
I painted my room.

24:15.219 --> 24:18.556
I took down all my shit.

24:18.590 --> 24:20.859
I thought I was different.

24:20.892 --> 24:23.628
I felt different.

24:23.662 --> 24:26.364
You're tethered to your room
because of what it represents,

24:26.397 --> 24:27.432
not what it looks like.

24:27.465 --> 24:28.566
It doesn't represent anything.

24:28.600 --> 24:30.334
It's a fucking room.

24:30.368 --> 24:32.370
It's where you feel safe.

24:32.404 --> 24:35.473
Without a place to go back to,
in the beginning,

24:35.507 --> 24:36.774
we'd be lost.

24:36.808 --> 24:39.443
At least that's how I've...

24:39.477 --> 24:42.280
rationalized it for myself.

24:42.314 --> 24:44.115
So what's yours?

24:44.148 --> 24:47.452
Well...

24:47.485 --> 24:49.588
apartment I grew up in,

24:49.621 --> 24:51.656
but I don't go back there
anymore.

24:52.390 --> 24:53.992
Why not?

24:55.660 --> 24:57.229
Something happened,

24:57.262 --> 24:59.865
and it stopped feeling
like it used to.

25:03.067 --> 25:06.204
So I can break it,

25:06.238 --> 25:10.508
this...tether connection,
whatever.

25:10.541 --> 25:14.412
I did, but it's not
an easy trade,

25:14.446 --> 25:17.282
losing safety for freedom.

25:18.916 --> 25:20.252
[SIGHS]

25:20.285 --> 25:22.988
Why do our bodies
do such weird shit?

25:25.090 --> 25:26.725
I don't know.

25:34.498 --> 25:36.835
What do you think we are?

25:38.603 --> 25:40.272
Fuck if I know.

25:43.642 --> 25:47.545
Are you not
even curious at all?

25:47.579 --> 25:50.315
I'm not sure if it'd change
anything if I knew.

25:51.349 --> 25:53.151
So that's it?

25:54.285 --> 25:56.520
Hey...

25:56.554 --> 25:59.156
you know more than I did
when I was your age,

25:59.190 --> 26:00.658
and I didn't have somebody

26:00.692 --> 26:02.727
who'd been through
this shit before.

26:03.594 --> 26:07.198
I had an uncle

26:07.231 --> 26:10.067
who was scared of me.

26:10.101 --> 26:12.003
Thought I was Moroi,

26:12.036 --> 26:13.805
a ghost.

26:16.474 --> 26:18.310
Not exactly
an inspiring thought.

26:22.714 --> 26:24.916
What about an angel?

26:26.818 --> 26:28.954
Do you feel like an angel?

26:31.089 --> 26:33.191
No.

26:34.592 --> 26:36.961
Yeah.

26:36.994 --> 26:38.697
Me neither.

26:42.767 --> 26:44.568
FISHER: After Mr. Boone
shot you...

26:44.602 --> 26:45.603
CLEO: I don't remember
anything.

26:45.637 --> 26:47.472
I woke up in the hospital.

26:47.505 --> 26:49.507
FISHER: And you didn't
regain consciousness

26:49.540 --> 26:51.041
at any point before that?

26:49.540 --> 26:51.041
HENRY: Cops?

26:51.075 --> 26:53.211
CLEO: No, not until
after the surgery.

26:54.446 --> 26:56.881
Oh, Henrietta.

26:59.684 --> 27:01.886
Sheriff Fisher.

27:01.919 --> 27:04.989
CLEO: Apparently
there have been some new
developments in the case.

27:05.022 --> 27:06.691
You mind if I ask you
a couple questions?

27:06.724 --> 27:08.159
Is there a better time
to do this?

27:08.192 --> 27:11.028
It's a school night.

27:08.192 --> 27:11.028
Oh, and I appreciate that.

27:11.061 --> 27:13.164
We have reason to believe
there was a struggle

27:13.197 --> 27:14.865
here at the house.

27:14.899 --> 27:18.102
I already talked
to Anna Hulce about that.

27:18.136 --> 27:20.805
Unfortunately
the former sheriff

27:20.839 --> 27:23.107
wasn't in her best state
of mind to execute her duties,

27:23.141 --> 27:25.543
so I'm taking over.

27:25.576 --> 27:27.078
Well, you've already
took our statements.

27:28.679 --> 27:32.083
Yes, but we want
to wrap the case up.

27:32.117 --> 27:34.652
Yeah, keep things local
before the feds get involved.

27:34.685 --> 27:38.222
I imagine you folks want...
want that as well.

27:38.255 --> 27:42.193
See, the truth is, Henry,

27:42.226 --> 27:44.562
we got 25 guys out there,

27:44.595 --> 27:46.864
and they are working
day in and day out.

27:46.898 --> 27:49.634
They're combing the woods,
knocking on doors,

27:49.667 --> 27:51.703
but they don't have any leads.

27:53.270 --> 27:55.473
I'm just wondering
if I'm wasting my time.

27:55.506 --> 27:56.574
Hey.

27:56.607 --> 27:58.676
What are you suggesting?

27:58.710 --> 28:01.112
[TENSE MUSIC]

28:01.146 --> 28:03.581
What happened to Bill Boone?

28:01.146 --> 28:03.581
Are you serious?

28:03.614 --> 28:04.815
I don't believe this.

28:04.849 --> 28:06.851
Bill came into our house
with a gun.

28:06.885 --> 28:09.119
He shot me
and abducted my daughter.

28:09.153 --> 28:12.123
We are the victims here.

28:09.153 --> 28:12.123
How 'bout this, huh?

28:12.156 --> 28:15.193
I'll take a quick look around,
and then we'll get settled.

28:15.226 --> 28:16.728
Have you got a warrant?

28:16.761 --> 28:19.063
Well, there's no need
for that yet, Mr. Hope.

28:19.096 --> 28:20.798
I'm just keeping things
friendly.

28:20.832 --> 28:23.534
Oh, okay, well, in that case,
I will ask you

28:23.567 --> 28:27.172
with a big, friendly smile,
get the fuck out of our house.

28:31.209 --> 28:32.743
All right.

28:32.776 --> 28:36.113
I'll get that warrant.
I'll be seeing you soon.

28:36.147 --> 28:37.915
You folks have
a good night, now.

28:37.948 --> 28:40.517
THOMAS:
Yes, yes, thank you.

28:40.551 --> 28:44.621
[DOOR OPENS]

28:44.655 --> 28:46.157
[DOOR SLAMS]

28:46.191 --> 28:48.125
What are we gonna do?
They're gonna search our house.

28:48.158 --> 28:50.561
It's okay.
They won't find anything.

28:50.594 --> 28:53.131
Are you sure?

28:50.594 --> 28:53.131
Yes.

28:54.632 --> 28:57.235
I'm, like, 90% sure.

28:57.268 --> 28:59.938
Okay, no, I can't...
I can't do this anymore.

28:59.971 --> 29:02.840
How can you keep doing this?

28:59.971 --> 29:02.840
I don't have a choice.

29:02.873 --> 29:06.478
What if...what if we just
tell them the truth?

29:07.811 --> 29:10.181
No, not the cops.
Our parents.

29:11.749 --> 29:13.784
If we tell them about Bill,

29:13.817 --> 29:15.820
we have to tell them about me.

29:15.853 --> 29:19.623
Okay, but your mom loves you.
She'll accept who you are.

29:19.657 --> 29:22.226
I don't even know
what I am.

29:22.259 --> 29:24.162
And she already treats me
like there's something
fucking wrong with me.

29:24.195 --> 29:26.730
If she knew the truth,
she would never be able

29:26.764 --> 29:27.899
to look at me again.

29:29.700 --> 29:32.137
Maybe she'd think
you're so much cooler.

29:37.041 --> 29:39.577
How would I even say it?

29:39.611 --> 29:41.679
"I teleport."

29:41.712 --> 29:44.149
Or, "I'm a teleporter."

29:47.352 --> 29:51.256
Nikolai said that
we might be ghosts.

29:52.489 --> 29:54.092
And Lucas thinks I'm an angel.

29:54.892 --> 29:56.594
Wait, Lucas Boone?

29:56.628 --> 29:58.796
Yeah, he found me
at the dance.

29:58.829 --> 30:00.264
What?
Why didn't you say anything?

30:00.297 --> 30:02.433
Because it's...
it's fine, I think.

30:02.466 --> 30:03.901
He just wanted to talk

30:03.934 --> 30:05.670
or check on me, protect me.

30:05.703 --> 30:07.204
I don't fucking know.

30:07.238 --> 30:10.942
Apparently he's religious now,
like, really religious.

30:10.975 --> 30:14.078
And he thinks you're an angel.

30:15.345 --> 30:17.048
[SIGHS]

30:20.585 --> 30:22.887
Could be worse.

30:22.920 --> 30:25.256
He could think
I was the devil.

30:26.223 --> 30:27.859
Right.

30:29.527 --> 30:31.095
Jenna.

30:31.129 --> 30:33.364
I...I will figure
something out,

30:33.397 --> 30:36.033
and we will get through this
like we always do,

30:36.066 --> 30:38.235
but we have to stick together.

30:38.269 --> 30:41.806
Please, don't say
anything to anyone.

30:41.839 --> 30:45.442
I'm not ready
for what that might do

30:45.476 --> 30:48.779
to all of us.

30:48.813 --> 30:51.215
Okay, I won't.

30:51.248 --> 30:54.852
Okay.

30:54.885 --> 30:57.222
But the cops aren't
gonna just go away.

30:59.223 --> 31:00.425
I know.

31:04.228 --> 31:06.264
[GLASSES SINGING]
<i> ♪ Now it's over ♪</i>

31:06.998 --> 31:08.766
<i> ♪ Yeah-ah-ah ♪</i>

31:08.799 --> 31:10.901
[SLURPING]

31:10.935 --> 31:13.637
Hey, what level clearance
did they give you?

31:13.670 --> 31:15.440
Orange.

31:15.473 --> 31:17.441
Right.
[CHUCKLES] Right.

31:17.474 --> 31:20.511
I forgot, it's been so long
since my training.

31:20.545 --> 31:22.113
What level are you?

31:24.381 --> 31:25.950
Orange.

31:27.351 --> 31:29.453
Okay, so...

31:29.487 --> 31:30.922
the same.

31:30.955 --> 31:33.857
It's not an easy job.
It's pretty hard.

31:33.891 --> 31:36.026
My last partner
couldn't cut it.

31:36.060 --> 31:38.496
Now he's at corporate
pushing papers.

31:38.529 --> 31:39.697
[SCOFFS]

31:39.730 --> 31:41.933
So, like, a promotion?

31:43.801 --> 31:46.337
No, I mean, that's not
what he called it.

31:46.370 --> 31:48.906
That would be a promotion
if he's at corporate now.

31:48.939 --> 31:51.342
It's not...

31:48.939 --> 31:51.342
[LOUD CLATTER]

31:51.376 --> 31:53.177
Fuck was that?

31:53.210 --> 31:54.812
Stay here.

31:53.210 --> 31:54.812
I'll come with you.

31:54.846 --> 31:55.980
No, no, no, no, no.

31:56.013 --> 31:58.582
Rookie, I got it.

31:58.616 --> 32:01.519
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC]

32:01.552 --> 32:03.488
[SCUFFLING]

32:11.996 --> 32:15.099
[GLASSES GROANING]

32:22.674 --> 32:24.509
[GROANS]
[WHISPERING] Behind you.

32:26.610 --> 32:28.880
Who the fuck are you?

32:28.913 --> 32:30.781
GLASSES: She's my new partner.

32:30.814 --> 32:32.317
Gun.

32:35.686 --> 32:37.455
Where's the Factor?

32:37.488 --> 32:39.991
Oh, come on, man,
you know we can't do that.

32:40.024 --> 32:42.993
Requires a call-in.
We're radio silent.

32:43.027 --> 32:44.161
[GROANING]

32:44.194 --> 32:45.896
[WHOOSHING]

32:44.194 --> 32:45.896
[GUNSHOT]

32:45.929 --> 32:49.366
Oh, fuck!

32:45.929 --> 32:49.366
Oh, God.

32:49.400 --> 32:52.203
[GROANING]

32:52.236 --> 32:53.571
[SIGHS]

32:53.604 --> 32:57.241
Oh, fuck you.
[GROANING]

32:58.276 --> 33:00.945
Factor.

32:58.276 --> 33:00.945
Elaine will kill me.

33:00.978 --> 33:03.281
Okay, okay.

33:05.149 --> 33:06.617
You motherfucker.

33:13.558 --> 33:15.459
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC]

33:15.492 --> 33:16.461
Hurry.

33:18.662 --> 33:20.264
That's all we have left.

33:25.803 --> 33:28.473
I'd stop waiting on Elaine
and start looking
for a new job.

33:29.707 --> 33:31.342
Dick!

33:31.375 --> 33:34.178
[WHOOSHING]

33:36.948 --> 33:40.051
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

33:46.991 --> 33:49.560
[GROANS]

33:56.067 --> 34:00.004
[EERIE MUSIC]

34:00.037 --> 34:02.206
Shit.

34:09.079 --> 34:11.882
[BELL RINGS]

34:11.916 --> 34:14.052
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

34:21.626 --> 34:22.593
Hey.

34:23.861 --> 34:25.596
Are you okay?

34:26.964 --> 34:29.533
Um, I don't know.

34:29.567 --> 34:31.736
Last night...

34:31.769 --> 34:33.804
last night, I got a message.

34:33.838 --> 34:36.440
Excuse me, Jenna,
can I steal you for a minute?

34:36.473 --> 34:37.542
Um...

34:38.943 --> 34:41.846
Sure, of course.

34:42.813 --> 34:44.482
I'll call you later?

34:47.818 --> 34:50.721
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

34:54.324 --> 34:57.160
Can I ask what this is about?

34:57.194 --> 34:59.029
We'll explain soon enough.

34:59.063 --> 35:01.398
[TENSE MUSIC]

35:01.431 --> 35:02.834
Miss Hope.

35:06.037 --> 35:07.738
Please have a seat.

35:09.106 --> 35:11.142
Am I in trouble?

35:16.780 --> 35:18.415
LUCAS: Hey.

35:18.449 --> 35:19.650
Hey.

35:24.187 --> 35:26.324
I'm glad that you called.

35:29.960 --> 35:31.863
Do you wanna...

35:29.960 --> 35:31.863
Yeah.

35:41.071 --> 35:43.207
[LUCAS SIGHS]

35:55.986 --> 35:58.923
It's a shitty feeling, right?

36:04.228 --> 36:07.298
Looking at me...

36:07.331 --> 36:08.432
and seeing him.

36:10.801 --> 36:12.236
Yeah.

36:13.971 --> 36:15.473
Yeah, I get it.

36:18.708 --> 36:23.381
With Esther...
Esther Miller, Amos' mom...

36:26.049 --> 36:28.753
[SIGHS]
I'd see him all the time.

36:30.988 --> 36:32.924
It's permanent.

36:36.127 --> 36:38.696
Taking a life.

36:42.666 --> 36:44.902
That's...

36:44.935 --> 36:47.205
that's my fault, too, Lucas.

36:48.238 --> 36:51.241
I'm...I'm the one
who pointed him out, so...

36:51.275 --> 36:53.211
It's not your fault.

36:54.645 --> 36:56.280
It's not, Henry.

36:57.848 --> 36:59.416
Listen, I need your help.

36:59.450 --> 37:01.885
Yeah, of course.
Anything.

37:01.918 --> 37:04.455
What...what do you need?

37:07.992 --> 37:09.993
This cop Fisher
came by the house,

37:10.027 --> 37:12.596
and he was asking questions.

37:12.629 --> 37:16.634
I think he's close
to figuring out
what happened to your dad.

37:20.103 --> 37:22.172
Uh, okay.

37:22.205 --> 37:23.374
What does he know?

37:25.643 --> 37:28.245
He found blood,

37:28.278 --> 37:30.981
um, your dad's blood,

37:31.015 --> 37:34.852
and I don't know what else,
but he's getting
a search warrant.

37:39.390 --> 37:42.426
Could you call him and say
that you've seen your dad?

37:43.827 --> 37:47.330
That he came to you

37:47.364 --> 37:49.933
after he left my house

37:49.966 --> 37:52.269
and that he's, um...

37:52.302 --> 37:54.171
that he's alive
and out there somewhere?

37:54.205 --> 37:55.806
I think he'll believe you.

37:58.508 --> 38:00.644
Yeah, but where
do I say he went?

38:00.677 --> 38:03.547
And then what happens when
they don't find him there?

38:03.581 --> 38:05.816
I don't know. I'm just...

38:05.849 --> 38:08.752
This is gonna buy me some time,
so that's all I need.

38:08.786 --> 38:11.188
And then what?

38:11.221 --> 38:13.357
Maybe he'll keep going
in that direction.

38:13.390 --> 38:16.927
I don't know. I just need
to get him off my back
so that I can figure it out.

38:21.331 --> 38:23.367
There's another way...

38:26.103 --> 38:28.039
To stop Fisher...

38:30.106 --> 38:34.745
Just make...all of this

38:34.778 --> 38:36.747
go away.

38:47.291 --> 38:49.393
<i> But you need to trust me.</i>

38:53.964 --> 38:55.866
ANNA: Shit.

39:04.741 --> 39:08.746
We, uh...we need
more packing tape.

39:10.247 --> 39:11.749
Okay.

39:15.051 --> 39:16.887
Take a walk with me.

39:26.330 --> 39:28.766
Look, I know
what you're thinking.

39:28.799 --> 39:32.002
I'm a disgrace
to the uniform.

39:32.035 --> 39:35.373
I messed up at home with Ortez.
I came here. I made it worse.

39:37.541 --> 39:39.877
I know you blame me
for Ortez's death.

39:42.079 --> 39:45.015
I think about him every day.

39:45.048 --> 39:47.818
I didn't see what happened.
I wish I did, but I didn't.

39:47.852 --> 39:49.787
My struggle with you, Anna,
is not with what you saw

39:49.820 --> 39:52.188
or didn't see,
it's with what you know.

39:52.222 --> 39:54.791
You didn't trust
your instincts.

39:54.825 --> 39:56.660
You didn't assert
what you knew was true.

39:56.694 --> 39:59.763
I didn't see William
shoot Ortez.
That's the truth.

39:59.796 --> 40:02.465
What was I supposed to...

39:59.796 --> 40:02.465
What truth is more important?

40:02.499 --> 40:04.368
The fact that a kid was shot

40:04.401 --> 40:06.970
in cold blood
for the color of his skin

40:07.003 --> 40:09.106
or that you were facing
the other way when it happened?

40:11.474 --> 40:13.911
Well, if I had said something,

40:13.944 --> 40:15.912
what difference
would it have made?

40:15.946 --> 40:17.347
My partner still would
have gotten off,

40:17.381 --> 40:19.049
whether I saw him or not.

40:19.082 --> 40:21.451
I would have lied under oath.

40:21.485 --> 40:22.752
Either way,
I would have let you down.

40:22.786 --> 40:24.621
I didn't raise you
to make me proud.

40:24.654 --> 40:27.892
I raised you to figure out
what that means for yourself.

40:29.660 --> 40:33.330
I'm sorry, Anna, but you're
held to a different standard.

40:33.363 --> 40:35.332
So the choices you make
will always be harder,

40:35.365 --> 40:37.401
but you have to make them.

40:37.434 --> 40:39.470
You left the city with regrets.

40:39.503 --> 40:41.672
Don't leave here the same way.

40:41.705 --> 40:44.208
No matter
what people are saying,

40:44.241 --> 40:48.779
you are gonna have to live
with yourself.

40:52.182 --> 40:54.651
<i> ♪ Baby, you see</i>

40:54.684 --> 40:57.287
<i> ♪ You're so right for me</i>

40:57.320 --> 40:59.789
<i> ♪ And I'm right for you</i>

40:59.823 --> 41:02.592
<i> ♪ I love the things you do</i>

41:02.625 --> 41:05.195
<i> ♪ Like sweet-tasting wine</i>

41:05.228 --> 41:07.731
<i> ♪ Your lips are so divine</i>

41:07.764 --> 41:10.400
<i> ♪ Your loving turns me on</i>

41:10.433 --> 41:12.903
<i> ♪ My lonely days are gone</i>

41:12.936 --> 41:17.441
<i> ♪ That's why I'm never
